CommentBody:
this is the line used to calculate the "Last usage > 6 months"
https://github.com/netwrix/pingcastle/blob/2d9ab43ba1f4343f5daa983a840a7de08bf28378/Healthcheck/Healthcheck.cs#L367

Also, you can see a few lines above, that the GenerateUserData method uses the lastLogonTimeStamp property.
https://github.com/netwrix/pingcastle/blob/2d9ab43ba1f4343f5daa983a840a7de08bf28378/Healthcheck/Healthcheck.cs#L309

Then, something important to mention, is that LastLogonTimeStamp can be up to around 9-14 days out of date. Microsoft does this to limit replication traffic.
You can check this article explaining that in more details: 
​​​​​​​https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/ask-the-directory-services-team/8220-the-lastlogontimestamp-attribute-8221-8211-8220-what-it-was/ba-p/396204 ​​​​​​​
